Conclusion: Between a guitar‑forward anthology that still preserves studio performances and extended instrumental detail (with some grit) and a live multi‑set suffering from heavy reverb, distant vocals and uneven sequencing, the Black Sabbath anthology (Symptom of the Universe) aligns better overall with my documented preferences and avoids the specific production and sequencing problems that I most dislike in the live compilation.

